* [[Balance_series|Balance]], EQ Recordings' electronic music CD serie

== Science and medicine ==

* [[Balance (ability)]], an ability to maintain balance (see also: [[Equilibrioception]])
* [[Balance disorder]], the loss of natural balance which can be caused by various medical conditions
* [[Balance (networking)|''Balance'' (networking)]], a popular piece of software for load balancing
* [[Balanced line]] in audio and telecommunications
* [[Load balancing (electrical power)]], the balance of electricity generation and consumption to minimise loss of unused generated electricity
* The neutral [[equilibrium point]] state in structural stability
* [[Chlordiazepoxide]], by the [[trade name]] ''Balance''

== Other uses ==

* [[Balance (accounting)]]
* [[Balance (metaphysics)]], a desirable point between two or more opposite forces
* [[Balance (film)|''Balance'' (film)]], a 1989 Academy Award–winning short animated film
* &quot;Balance&quot;, a poem by Patti Smith from her book ''[[kodak (book)|kodak]]''
* [[Balance (advertisement)]], a 1989 award-winning television advertisement for the Lexus LS 400
* [[Balancing in international relations|Balancing]] (or &quot;hard balancing&quot;) in international relations
* In grammar, [[balancing and deranking|balancing]] refers to the use in subordinate clauses of verb forms identical to those in main clauses

