===Financial performance===
In 2008 the Brisbane Lions recorded a loss of $2,200,200.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite news| url=http://www.news.com.au/couriermail/sport/afl/story/0,27046,24775628-5016169,00.html }} {{Dead link|date=August 2010|bot=RjwilmsiBot}}&lt;/ref&gt; CEO Michael Bowers was reported to be &quot;buoyed&quot; when 2009 membership exceeded its 2008 total by 8 April 2009.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite news| url=http://www.news.com.au/heraldsun/story/0,21985,25321644-19746,00.html?from=public_rss | title=Lions hit by fall in corporate box sales | first=Greg | last=Davis | date=12 April 2009 | work=Sunday Herald Sun}}&lt;/ref&gt; In 2009 the Brisbane Lions recorded a further loss of $603,207.&lt;ref&gt;http://sportal.com.au/afl-news-display/lions-record-big-financial-loss-81769&lt;/ref&gt;

==Club symbols==
===Guernseys===
[[File:BrisLionsDesign.png|thumb|200px|Home guernsey (top), away guernsey (middle), clash guernsey (bottom)]]

The three types of guernsey are:

*Home guernsey (worn since [[2010 AFL season|2010]]): Maroon and blue based guernsey with a lion, coloured gold and maroon. [[Bank of Queensland]] sponsor on front and [[Conergy]] sponsor on back (home pants worn in home games and away pants worn in away games not played in Victoria).

*Away guernsey (Worn since [[2010 AFL season|2010]]): Red and blue based guernsey with a lion, coloured gold and red. [[Conergy]] sponsor on front and [[Bank of Queensland]] sponsor on back (away pants worn).

*Clash guernsey (Worn since [[2010 AFL season|2010]]): Maroon, white and blue based guernsey with a lion, coloured gold and maroon.  [[Conergy]] sponsor on front and [[Bank of Queensland]] sponsor on back (away pants worn).
[[File:Lions mascot.jpg|thumb|70px|left|Bernie Gabba Vegas]]

===Mascot===
The Lion's [[Mascot Manor]] representative and club mascot is Bernie &quot;Gabba&quot; Vegas, a caricature of a lion dressed in Brisbane Lions jumper, sunglasses, wide lapels and flares, designed to resemble [[Elvis Presley]].

===Song===
The music of the team song is the same as that of [[La Marseillaise]], the French national anthem.

''We are the pride of Brisbane town''
&lt;br /&gt;
''We wear maroon, blue and gold''
&lt;br /&gt;
''We will always fight for victory''
&lt;br /&gt;
''Like Fitzroy and Bears of old''
&lt;br /&gt;
''All for one and one for all''
&lt;br /&gt;
''We will answer to the call''
&lt;br /&gt;
''Go Lions, Brisbane Lions''
&lt;br /&gt;
''We’ll kick the winning score''
&lt;br /&gt;
